(1975, '2020-01-02 11:10:00.000000', 'Home IT Jobs Job details Job Database administrator - Houten Hoogheemraadschap De Stichtse Rijnlanden - Houten Hoogheemraadschap De Stichtse Rijnlanden MBO level 4 or higher Medior/Senior level Permanent contract 24 - 36 hours p/w MBO level 4 or higher Medior/Senior level Permanent contract € 2,887 - € 3,935 p/m 24 - 36 hours p/w Job status: open Apply now or register for free Or Save Mail WhatsApp Job saved in your favorites! Job removed from your favorites! Function description Do you have several years of experience in database management and are you ready for the next step in your development? Does it give you energy to work in a passionate team? Good, then we\'d love to talk to you! Because the automation team is looking for a colleague: Database administrator 24-36 hours p/w (Wooden) What you\'re going to do You are careful and accurate in your work. You are focused on creating a stable and efficient IT environment, where the database environments are specifically your responsibility. In daily practice, your tasks are: (Technical) management, maintenance, adaptation and renewal of the databases; You ensure optimal performance of the databases as well as their backup and the operation of adequate recovery procedures; Advising on setting up and configuring databases, associated links and applications in the preparation of projects; Support, advise and act as a point of contact for (functional) application managers and project staff. This will mainly relate to our ArcGIS environment in which we have recorded a lot of geographical information. Its proper functioning is crucial for our primary tasks as a water board. Want to know more about us? For more information see: https://www.werkenbijhdsr.nl/ read more Requirements Who are we? De Stichtse Rijnlanden provides safe dikes, clean water and dry feet in the southern part of the province of Utrecht and a small part of Zuid-Holland. Hoogheemraadschap De Stichtse Rijnlanden (HDSR) is one of the 21 water boards in the Netherlands. The water board, like a municipality, is a local authority. HDSR consists of a general board, a college of dike reeve and water boards and approximately 500 employees. What makes you successful? You are a careful and expert expert, interested in the environment in which you do your work. You are able to work pleasantly with others and communicate well and adequately. You want to develop yourself in the field, facilitated by us as an employer. Furthermore, you have / are you: A relevant ICT training at a minimum MBO-4 level; A minimum of 3 years of experience in a data management role; You have experience in working with Microsoft SQL Server; A connecting, proactive and steadfast colleague; You are so flexible that you are available (about once a month) outside regular working hours for updates or other activities. It\'s a plus if: You have an ICT education at HBO bachelor level; You have obtained Microsoft SQL server 2017 certification; You have knowledge of Oracle 12c databases; You have experience in working with Linux; Your knowledge of ODA; You have knowledge of TOAD or Oracle Developer. read more Language proficiency Must have: Dutch Salary info Gross € 2,887 - € 3,935 p/m Een salaris tussen € 2.887,- en € 3.935,- bruto per maand (Cao bedragen per 1-1-2020) en op basis van een 36-urige werkweek en schaal 9 van onze Sectorale Arbeidsvoorwaardenregelingen Waterschapspersoneel (SAW). read more Other info What can you count on? Of course, this challenging position requires an excellent reward, tailored to your experience and capabilities, and good fringe benefits: A salary between € 2,887 and € 3,935 gross per month (CAO amounts per 1-1-2020) and based on a 36-hour working week and scale 9 of our Sectoral Conditions of Employment for Waterboard Personnel (SAW). Individual choice budget of 20% that you can use at your own discretion, for example to buy extra days off. A working week of at least 24 and at most 36 hours. Flexible working hours and the ability to work independently of time and place. We work in a flexible office concept. An informal, non-hierarchical working atmosphere with attention for each other, committed colleagues and passion for working. An organisation where there is a lot of room for personal initiative and input, and where something is done with it. Opportunities to continue to develop within our water board. A personal training budget of € 5,000 has been set aside for this, which you can use within 5 years, in consultation with your manager. Within HDSR, the talent programme is the leitmotiv for the way in which employees do their work. This is based on the philosophy: unleash the best in yourself and in each other! Apply or know more? Or do you want to know more? For more information about this dike of a job, please contact Harold Toering (Automation team leader) on 030-209 7278. For questions about the procedure you can contact Gilian Gratama, at 030- 634 5923. Convinced? Surprise us today with your application! Click on the application button and immediately apply for the position of Database Administrator. We do not appreciate acquisition following this vacancy. read more Contact person Mr. Gilian Gratama Apply now or register for free Or Save Mail WhatsApp Job saved in your favorites! Job removed from your favorites!', 'Job Database administrator - Houten - ICTerGezocht.nl', 'https://www.ictergezocht.nl/en/5711_brandmannen/ict-vacatures/45059_databasebeheerder/', b'1', b'0', 'AFWACHTING', NULL, NULL, b'0'),
