(1977, '2020-01-02 11:10:07.000000', 'Home IT Jobs Job details Job ICT Infrastructure Specialist - Windows Server | VMWare | Cloud | Challenging projects - Hilversum Xiphos B.V. - Hilversum Xiphos B.V. Company profile MBO level 4 or higher Medior/Senior level Permanent contract / Secondment 40 hours p/w MBO level 4 or higher Medior/Senior level Permanent contract / Secondment € 3,000 - € 4,500 p/m 40 hours p/w Job status: open Apply now or register for free Or Save Mail WhatsApp Job saved in your favorites! Job removed from your favorites! Function description As an experienced System Administrator, you know a lot about Infrastructure and Microsoft, but you are also able to go into depth in various areas. Depending on your experience, we think in areas such as Microsoft, Virtualization, Exchange, Office 365, Cloud/Azure, Backups, etc. Our organization! Xiphos is an innovative, quality-driven IT service provider with a wide range of services. Xiphos provides temporary expertise, services and advice within the IT Infrastructure. Our mission is to enable our customers\' IT departments to add concrete and measurable value, which contributes to the improvement of their organisation. Function-Description You, as Mr/Sr System Administrator ICT projects, have often been on the 3rd (or maybe even 4th) line and, in addition to troubleshooting complex problems and disruptions, you have also gained experience in executing projects (e.g. migrations) and building and setting up Servers in combination with the virtualisation part that comes with it. WHATS IN IT FOR YOU? You get the chance to work at cool companies in different industries. From business services, IT organizations, the media world to healthcare and government. Organizations with challenging environments in all shapes and sizes, from about 500+ users (from Cloud, Hybrid, On premise to Virtual and physical servers). This not only allows you to learn quickly, but also allows you, if possible, to continue to develop your professional knowledge and personal skills right up to your retirement. Think of advising organizations based on your insights because you speak from experience of multiple (size) organizations so you can better assess the impact and see what can be improved in the organization. In general, you will work for organisations within your own region as much as possible, but you will be flexible in your approach and you will mainly go for the substantive challenge. Getting up laughing to go to work, that\'s what we do it for! Taking account of each other and travel time is part of that. You\'re changing assignments all the time. So just imagine that from 3-6 months or maybe 9-12 months you are temporarily providing an organization with your specific knowledge and are now working for a super nice employer who provides you with a safe home (with nice outings, drinks and attention to training & development). P.S. with us you are always busy keeping up with your technical knowledge, but if you have ambition you can either develop yourself or specialise in an all-round way with us. Think of Cloud and Azure or Virtualization with HyperV or/and VMware... or maybe a combination of both? read more Requirements You have a completed MBO 3/4 ICT training or equivalent technical training; You are in possession of an MCSA Server 2012 or higher, are working on it or are willing to achieve it in a short period of time; You are ITIL V3 (and nowadays it is already 4) certified, working on it or are willing to achieve it quickly; You speak Dutch and are in possession of a driving licence. read more Language proficiency Must have: Dutch, English Driving skills Must have: Car (B) Company description Xiphos is an innovative, quality-driven IT service provider with a wide range of services. Xiphos provides temporary expertise, services and advice within the IT Infrastructure. Our mission is to enable our customers\' IT departments to add concrete and measurable value, which contributes to the improvement of their organisation. read more Salary info Gross € 3,000 - € 4,500 p/m Salary is based on knowledge (certificates) and work experience. Other info In case of good performance, the possibility of a permanent employment contract; Active contribution to your technical development including bonus scheme for keeping your certificates up to date; 3 times a year a nice outing + interactive knowledge sessions and spontaneous drinks; 28 holidays, 5 study days and the possibility to buy (and earn) some extra money; 8.33% holiday pay (which is equivalent to a whole month\'s salary); A leased car (with fuel card) or travel allowance; A good pension scheme and monthly overtime payments. read more Contact person Ms. Sarah van Dorth 06-12239010 Apply now or register for free Or Save Mail WhatsApp Job saved in your favorites! Job removed from your favorites!', 'Job ICT Infrastructure Specialist - Windows Server | VMWare | Cloud | Challenging projects - Hilversum', 'https://www.ictergezocht.nl/en/5340_xiphos-bv/ict-vacatures/45046_ict-infrastructuur-specialist-windows-server-vmware-uitdagende-projecten/', b'1', b'0', 'AFWACHTING', NULL, NULL, b'0'),
(1979, '2020-01-02 11:10:20.000000', 'Home IT Jobs Job details Job Linux Platform Engineer - Driebergen-Rijssenburg (no posting or managed services) - Zeist Korndewal - Zeist Korndewal Company profile Auto didact or higher Junior/Medior/Senior level Permanent contract 32 - 40 hours p/w Auto didact or higher Junior/Medior/Senior level Permanent contract € 3,000 - € 4,750 p/m 32 - 40 hours p/w Job status: open Apply now or register for free Or Save Mail WhatsApp Job saved in your favorites! Job removed from your favorites! Function description Looking for a challenging in-house position at a software company where you are responsible for your own platform? Not a platform intended for Managed Services but an own environment intended to offer in-house developed software solutions? To expand our team we are looking for a Linux Engineer. As a Linux Engineer you will be responsible, together with an experienced Linux Specialist, for the further development, performance and security of a large hosting platform. A platform that facilitates between 100,000 - 150,000 users daily when using an in-house developed software solution that is offered as a SaaS solution. Due to the growth in the number of customers (and users), legislation and regulations for storing and storing data, there are increasingly high demands on the platform. You follow the developments in the market and translate them into concrete projects to improve the platform. Naturally, taking into account scalability and management in the future. As a Linux Engineer you are also responsible for an up-to-date platform. You set up new servers, monitor their performance and intervene when necessary. You are in regular contact with the development and test team but do not provide user support to customers. The physical servers (hardware in the data centre) are maintained by an external party. At the moment you are dealing with Linux (RHEL / CentOS), Bash Shell Scripting, SQL / PostgreSQL, VMware, Apache HTTPD, Apache Tomcat and Automation Tools like Puppet and Ansible. REST APIs in NodeJS of Python, SAML Signl Sign On and Intrusion Prevention and Detection Systems (IPS / IDP). read more Requirements A driven (future) Linux Engineer who is willing to learn a lot and contribute to the further development of the organization on a technical level. You have a broad basic theoretical knowledge in the form of a completed ICT course or recent, relevant work experience as a Linux Engineer. read more Language proficiency Must have: Dutch Company description An informal software company that offers a modular software solution from its own platform. The demand for the software solution has grown rapidly in recent years, as a result of which the organisation has grown by 15 people to now 50 colleagues. The team in which you will work consists of a number of consultants, software developers and testers. In your daily work you will mainly work with another Linux Specialist with whom you will be responsible for the platform. Within the organisation, professionals with a high level of knowledge often work. Staff turnover is minimal and the average employee works there for six to eight years. The vacancy that is currently open is to expand the team. read more Salary info Gross € 3,000 - € 4,750 p/m A permanent employment contract (no secondment) with a software company that invests a lot of time, money and energy in the further development of its products due to its growth. You can enrol at junior, medior or senior level with the necessary guidance, challenge and reward. - Permanent job for 32-40 hours a week; - Salary indication €3000-€4750 which is determined on the basis of knowledge and experience; - The opportunity to develop yourself internally as a senior Linux Specialist; - Supervision of an experienced Linux Specialist and the possibility to follow training courses; - Location that is easily accessible by car or public transport; - Naturally, holidays, holiday pay, pension scheme, laptop,